race.comment: BREMEL (1) made it three wins from just five career runs when she proved a little too strong for a Bm68 field over 1000m at Wyong last start. Maps beautifully behind a cracking tempo and she is good enough to round them up and add to her fine record. CASSEROUSSE (5) made it two from two this time in work when she led all the way and showed great fight to score over 1200m at Rosehill recently. Won't mind coming back in trip and doesn't spend a cent from the inside alley. STRADA VARENNA (3) knocked up after leading first-up at Rosehill last time out. Worth another chance dropping back to midweek company. FIORENZA (6)
